---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 334
Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Work, Action and Society=On ‘Karma’ and ‘Karma Yoga’
By: Sri Sankarâchârya
Commentary: By one who aspires after liberation which by its nature
  cannot be the result of any action (explanatory note added by the
  translator. Swâmi Jagadânanda).
---
The results of actions are the production, acquisition, transformation
and purification of something. They produce no other results. All
actions with their accessories should, therefore, be given up.
